@startuml
title Nexus Core Architecture and Trust Boundaries

package "Nexus Core Release Package\nTrusted Platform Baseline" {
  package "Built-in Plugins\nIncluded, scanned, no separate review" as BuiltIn
  package "Official Plugins\nRepo-maintained, release-governed, no separate review" as Official

  package "Nexus Core Platform" {
    [Workspace/UI Layer]
    [Framework Layer\nPyQt5 wrappers + enhanced widgets]
    [Runtime Layer\nPlugin discovery + manifest loading]
    [Core Services\nEventBus, DataStore, Command, Context]
  }
}

package "External Plugins\nSeparate organizational review required" as External #fff7ed

BuiltIn --> [Runtime Layer]
Official --> [Runtime Layer]
External ..> [Runtime Layer] : controlled boundary

[Nexus Core Platform] --> [Python 3.8+ / PyQt5 / Local OS + Filesystem]

note right of External
External plugins are not included in
the Nexus Core release package and
are outside Nexus Core governance.
end note

note bottom of [Nexus Core Platform]
No outbound network calls by default.
Local filesystem persistence.
In-process Python execution.
CodeQL + Dependabot enabled.
end note

@enduml
